this act shall be called the indian pena: This Act shall be called the Indian Penal Code, and shall extend to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir
the pronoun he and its derivatives are u: The pronoun he and its derivatives are used for any person whether male or female
in every part of this code, except where: In every part of this Code, except where a contrary intention appears from the context, words which refer to acts done extend also to illegal omissions
no person shall be punished for any offe: No person shall be punished for any offence
extension of code to extra-territorial o: Extension of Code to extra-territorial offences
title and extent of operation of the cod: Title and extent of operation of the Code
punishment of offences committed beyond,: Punishment of offences committed beyond, but which by law may be tried within, India
a person is said to do a thing fraudulen: A person is said to do a thing fraudulently if he does that thing with intent to defraud but not otherwise
